Hope you can read the kana from my computer.<br>
<br>
--から and the comma " , " :<br>
The comma is always after, not before から.<br>
I guess there are some occasions to actually drop the comma.<br>
Note : You can say ので instead of から　for a softer cause-effect sentence.<br>
<br>
--高った<br>
Should be 高かった (takakatta)<br>
You take the final い of the い adjectives and replace by かった.<br>
Even if that sounds strange.<br>
eg. あたたかい (warm) will be あたたかかった. Lots of "a" !<br>
<br>
--裕子だ、からかわいい<br>
I don't understand this sentence. Did you mean "Since 裕子 was here, it was cool" ?<br>
かわいい means "pretty, cute". For "Cool, great" you can say よかった (the かった form of いい is based on its synonym よい).<br>
<br>
--うろさかった<br>
Should be うるさかった。(replace RO by RU).<br>
<br>
--いねだったから、うるさかった<br>
Would mean, "because it was a dog, it was noisy".<br>
For "Because there was a dog", you can say いぬ　が　いた　から<br>
with いた the た form of いる ("exists" for the living persons).<br>
<br>
<br>
But your best counsellor in Japanese will always be a native Japanese ;)<br>
<br>
Keep up the good work !<br>
For someone who almost didn't know any word in Japanese, in less than a year you're doing well, I think.<br>
