3-INU DATTA KARA, UROSAKATTA<br>
should be urUsakatta.<br>
However, saying this would mean "since it was a dog, it was noisy".<br>
If you wanted to say "since there was a dog, it was noisy" you can say<br>
INU GA ITA KARA, URUSAKATTA<br>
ITA being the -TA form of the (iru---imasu) verb (to exist, for living things).<br>
